    <main>
        <section id="home">
            <h2>Welcome to Phishing Awareness</h2>
            <p>Phishing is a fraudulent attempt to obtain sensitive information by disguising as a trustworthy entity. This website provides information on how to recognize and avoid phishing attacks.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="common-tactics">
            <h2>Common Phishing Tactics</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Email Phishing: Fake emails that look real.</li>
                <li>Spear Phishing: Targeted attacks on specific individuals.</li>
                <li>Whaling: Attacks on high-profile individuals like executives.</li>
                <li>Vishing: Phishing through voice calls.</li>
                <li>Smishing: Phishing via SMS messages.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="recognize">
            <h2>How to Recognize Phishing</h2>
            <p>Look for the following signs:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Unusual sender email addresses</li>
                <li>Generic greetings (e.g., "Dear User")</li>
                <li>Urgency or threats in the message</li>
                <li>Links that donâ€™t match the expected URL</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="avoid">
            <h2>How to Avoid Phishing</h2>
            <p>Follow these best practices:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Always verify the sender's identity.</li>
                <li>Do not click on suspicious links.</li>
                <li>Use two-factor authentication when available.</li>
                <li>Keep your software and antivirus updated.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="report">
            <h2>Reporting Phishing</h2>
            <p>If you encounter a phishing attempt, report it to your email provider or local authorities. You can also check with official organizations like the FTC.</p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>Contact us for more information: info@phishingawareness.com</p>
    </footer>
